init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the â€œLost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: In the year 2045, the world is a very different place.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The population has exploded to the point where there is no more room on Earth.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The rich have moved to the moon, and the rest of the population has been left to fend for themselves.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The only way to get to the moon is to win a lottery.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The lottery is held every year, and the odds of winning are one in a million.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You live off the land, and you have a small garden.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: One day, you discover that the rich are hunting humans.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You must survive the hunters, and the other dangers of the wilderness.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You must also find a way to get to the moon, and win the lottery.
